n Friday and specifically mentioned Algeria's Khelif, who won the women's welterweight gold at the Paris Olympics last year and prompted a gender-eligibility row.\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9987891789904408, \"rank\": 0.0012106982761831732, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Boxing\", \"from\": 366, \"to\": 378}, {\"ngram\": \"the new policy\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 403}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's welterweight gold\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"a gender-eligibility row\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Imane Khelif may not participate in the female category at \\u2026 any World Boxing event until Imane Khelif undergoes genetic sex screening in accordance with World Boxing's rules and testing procedures,\\\" the organisation said in a statement.\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 570, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 730, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9998983316365065, \"rank\": 0.00010167486454761868, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 625}, {\"ngram\": \"any World Boxing event\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"genetic sex screening\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 704}, {\"ngram\": \"accordance\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"testing procedures\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisation\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 806}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"World Boxing has written to the Algerian Boxing Federation to inform it that Imane Khelif will not be allowed to participate in the female category at the Eindhoven Box Cup or any World Boxing event until Imane Khelif undergoes sex testing,\\\" it added.\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 1061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 842, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9875294150405034, \"rank\": 0.007837041844988554, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 851, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9998983316365065, \"rank\": 0.00010167486454761868, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Boxing\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 822}, {\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eindhoven Box Cup\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"any World Boxing event\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1027}, {\"ngram\": \"sex testing\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Boxing is responsible for organising bouts at the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics, after being granted provisional recognition by the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1197, \"end\": 1228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Boxing\", \"from\": 1063, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"bouts\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1111}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"provisional recognition\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the new policy, all athletes above the age of 18 who want to participate in a World Boxing-owned or sanctioned competition will need to undergo a PCR, or polymerase chain reaction genetic test, to determine what sex they were at birth and their eligibility to compete.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\", \"score\": 0.7013735407063533, \"rank\": 0.36439022803953214, \"text\": \"PCR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new policy\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1251}, {\"ngram\": \"all athletes\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"a World Boxing-owned or sanctioned competition\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1359}, {\"ngram\": \"polymerase\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"chain reaction genetic test\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1429}, {\"ngram\": \"what sex\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The PCR test is a laboratory technique used to detect specific genetic material, in this case the SRY gene, that reveals the presence of the Y chromosome, which is an indicator of biological sex.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1511, \"end\": 1519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\", \"score\": 0.9978205803074631, \"rank\": 0.0021841799373301975, \"text\": \"PCR test\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a laboratory technique\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"specific genetic material\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1586}, {\"ngram\": \"this case\", \"from\": 1591, \"to\": 1600}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"the Y chromosome\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"an indicator\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"biological sex\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1701}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The test can be conducted by a nasal or mouth swab, or by taking a sample of saliva or blood.\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The test\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"a nasal or mouth swab\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"a sample\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"saliva\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"blood\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1796}]}, {\"sentence\": \"National federations will be responsible for testing and will be required to confirm the sex of their athletes when entering them into World Boxing competitions by producing certification of their chromosomal sex, as determined by a PCR test.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2038, \"end\": 2046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\", \"score\": 0.9978205803074631, \"rank\": 0.0021841799373301975, \"text\": \"PCR test\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_testing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"National federations\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"testing\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"the sex\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"their athletes\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"World Boxing competitions\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1965}, {\"ngram\": \"certification\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"their chromosomal sex\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2017}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reuters news agency reported that Khelif could not be reached for comment, while the Algerian Boxing Federation did not immediately respond to questions about the development.\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2049, \"end\": 2056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999998458406, \"rank\": 1.5420559131095694e-10, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 2134, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9875294150405034, \"rank\": 0.007837041844988554, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9998983316365065, \"rank\": 0.00010167486454761868, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 2083, 